                                                                    <h3>23. Marriage of ‘Umm Kulthum</h3>
                                    <a href="../../../../external.html?link=https://thaqalayn.net/book/5" class="btn btn-primary"><span data-feather="arrow-left-circle"></span> Back to book</a>
                                                                <hr>
                                                            <p class="libAr" dir="rtl">1- عَلِيُّ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ عَنْ أَبِيهِ عَنِ ابْنِ أَبِي عُمَيْرٍ عَنْ هِشَامِ بْنِ سَالِمٍ وَحَمَّادٍ عَنْ زُرَارَةَ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللهِ (عَلَيْهِ السَّلام) فِي تَزْوِيجِ أُمِّ كُلْثُومٍ فَقَالَ إِنَّ ذَلِكَ فَرْجٌ غُصِبْنَاهُ.</p>
                                <br>
                                
                                                            <p class="" dir="">1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn Salim and Hammad from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about the marriage of ‘Umm Kulthum has said, ‘It was a rape we suffered.”’ </p>
